            "text": "Finding the \"best\" melasma treatment in Houston depends on your skin type and the depth of your pigmentation (epidermal vs. dermal). Because Houston's heat and UV levels are major triggers, local specialists emphasize a combination approach: **topical suppression, professional peels, and \"cold\" lasers.**\n\n### **1. Top Specialized Clinics & Providers**\nSeveral Houston clinics are highly regarded for their specific focus on melasma and skin of color.\n\n*   **Dermatology & Laser Surgery Center (Dr. Paul Friedman):** A world-renowned expert in laser surgery. This clinic is a top choice if you are seeking advanced laser treatments like **PicoWay** or **Clear + Brilliant**, which are safer for melasma than traditional heat-heavy lasers.\n*   **Aesthetic Specialists of Houston (Dr. Angela Sturm):** Offers a comprehensive **\"Melasma Package\"** that bundles Clear + Brilliant laser, VI Peel, and microneedling with exosomes for a multi-layered approach.\n*   **TaraMD (Dr. Tara Akunna):** A specialist in **melanin-rich skin**. This is a critical choice if you have a darker skin tone, as incorrect melasma treatments (especially lasers) can often cause post-inflammatory hyperpigmentation (PIH) in darker skin.\n*   **M Spa Face and Body:** Known specifically for the **Melanage Peel**, a high-strength medicated mask designed specifically for stubborn melasma.\n*   **Village Dermatology:** Offers the **Melanage Mask Peel** and is one of the few clinics noted for managing resistant melasma with **oral Tranexamic Acid** when topicals fail.\n\n---\n\n### **2. Best Professional Procedures in Houston**\nHouston providers currently favor these three categories of treatment for long-term results:\n\n#### **Specialized Melasma Peels (The \"Gold Standard\")**\nThese are medicated masks applied in-office and worn for 4–10 hours.\n*   **Melanage Peel:** Highly effective for medium-depth melasma. Available at *M Spa Face and Body* and *Nigro Dermatology Group*.\n*   **Cosmelan Peel:** A world-famous depigmenting peel that inhibits melanin production at the source. Available at *Dr. Nikko Dermatology* and *Solace Med Spa*.\n*   **VI Peel Precision Plus:** A popular, lower-downtime option specifically for pigmentation. Available at *Utopia Plastic Surgery* and *myEvergreen MedSpa*.\n\n#### **\"Cold\" Laser Therapies**\nTraditional lasers (like IPL or Fraxel) can sometimes worsen melasma due to heat. Houston specialists often recommend:\n*   **Clear + Brilliant (Perméa):** Known as \"Baby Fraxel,\" it is gentle enough to treat melasma without triggering more pigment.\n*   **PicoSure / PicoWay:** These lasers use pressure waves rather than heat to shatter pigment, making them safer for many melasma patients. Found at *DermSurgery Associates* and *Inkfree, MD*.\n\n---\n\n### **3. Medical-Grade Topical & Oral Options**\nMost Houston dermatologists will start with a customized prescription regimen to \"quiet\" the pigment cells before performing procedures.\n*   **Triple Cream:** A prescription-strength blend of hydroquinone, a retinoid (tretinoin), and a mild steroid.\n*   **Cyspera:** A newer, hydroquinone-free alternative that is becoming popular for long-term maintenance.\n*   **Oral Tranexamic Acid:** Increasingly used by specialists like *Aviva Dermatology* and *Elite Dermatology* for \"vascular\" melasma that doesn't respond to creams.\n\n### **4. Summary Recommendation**\n*   **For Stubborn/Deep Melasma:** Look for a clinic that offers the **Melanage or Cosmelan Peel** (e.g., *M Spa* or *Village Dermatology*).\n*   **For Skin of Color:** Prioritize a specialist like **Dr. Tara Akunna (TaraMD)** or **Dr. Brundha Balaraman (Allustra Dermatology)**.\n*   **For Maintenance/Prevention:** Use a **tinted mineral sunscreen** with **Iron Oxides** (like EltaMD or SkinCeuticals), which protects against the blue light and heat common in the Houston climate.",
